rComments: Lots of music to listen to! Come into class with an open mind, and stay on top of your readings and you'll do well. Not arrogant at all. Very friendly and approachable. Responds to emails quickly and was willing to help out students at his office at the Music Library. Was a great course and would highly recommend to anyone interested in symphonies!

I came into the class with absolutely NO background knowledge in contemporary music, and Professor Neufeldt completely changed my life!!! Not only were his lectures insightful, but he kept them interesting with little jokes and youtube clips (Rob Paravonian anyone?). I went to see him during his office hours and he was SO kind, helpful, and friendl

He was knowledgeable but quite arrogant and seemed very distanced from the class. His desire to keep the course website secret from anyone outside the class and his paranoia about recording lectures was regrettable. He was a fair marker, but the exam was surprisingly challenging.
Very helpful prof - lectures are word for word taken from the text - No need to attend class.
